# mod_GLQS_readme
*clr & cla
'<b>Version 0.34.4 (stable) - Current</b>'
'- Fixed: The Misc clothing category (Give Everything, Buy By Store, and the per-item picker) granted a wall of blank, unlabeled clothing slots - as many as whatever category happened to run right before it internally. Root cause: this category was keyed to an array named misc, but the base game only ever defines images and descriptions for a differently-named misc_outfits array (which holds exactly one scripted item, not a real shop line) and has no official item count for misc at all, so the count silently carried over from the previous category in the buy-out list instead of stopping at zero. The broken Misc category has been removed entirely - there was never a real shop behind it to buy out.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.34.3</b>'
'- Fixed: Tattoo and piercing design pickers showed no images at all (or the wrong count) on the stable Girl Life 0.9.8.3 build. Root cause: the design count came from a get_total function that only exists on the newer Dev Life nightly build; stable only exposes a totals gosub that returns its value a different way, so the nightly-only call silently read a stale leftover number on stable, most often 0. Now reads the count through the convention both builds actually support.'
'- Fixed: A handful of specific clothing, bra and panty items (e.g. 2 Danilovich outfits, 1 Pussy-Cats dress, 3 G&M bras, 4 G&M panties) granted by this mod showed up as blank/broken images in the wardrobe on stable 0.9.8.3. These are dead slots the base games own shop already hides from players for exactly this reason - no real image exists behind them on stable - but this mods bulk-grant and single-item-pick options were granting every index blindly instead of respecting that exclusion list. Now skipped, matching what the base game itself already does.'
'- Changed: Internal consistency cleanup - shoe/bra/panty/bodysuit durability now goes through the same explicit fallback pattern as the clothing/coat fix in 0.34.2, instead of silently relying on an undefined nightly-only variable defaulting to 0. No player-visible change (stable has no durability tracking for these categories at all, so the value was already effectively 0).'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.34.2</b>'
'- Fixed: Every clothing and coat item granted by this mod (Give Everything, Buy All, per-category Give All, and single-item picks) was worn out on the stable Girl Life 0.9.8.3 build - usable and repairable, but instantly flagged as worn and needing a tailor. Root cause: durability was set from CloMaxStrength/CoatMaxStrength, variables the newer Dev Life nightly build computes but that do not exist at all on stable 0.9.8.3, so they silently read as 0 there. Now falls back to the same category-based formula stable itself uses when granting a purchase, so items come in undamaged on both builds. Shoes, bras, panties and bodysuits were not affected - stable 0.9.8.3 has no durability tracking for those categories at all.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.34.1</b>'
'- Changed: Quick Setup link no longer shows on the wardrobe screen or the shared clothing_view browsing/buying screen every store routes through - purely cosmetic, so it does not clutter these image-heavy screens. Nothing else depends on the link being present there.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.34</b>'
'- Added: School Grades has a Zero Absences button, separate from Set All Grades to 100, matching the base games own Zero Absenteeism cheat menu option.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.33</b>'
'- Fixed: Fame By Region (individual activity Max buttons and Max All (this region)) silently did nothing for every activity except Sex, Prostitution and Flashing - those three looked unaffected only because they already carry decent fame from normal gameplay, not because the buttons worked. Root cause: fame_detail killed the captured region variable at the end of its own render, before the player could click any button that used it, so every max click ran with an empty region and wrote to a bogus fame key instead of the real one. This is the same stray-killvar bug the v0.28 changelog already fixed once; the v0.29.4 shared-data-table refactor reintroduced it here.'
'- Fixed: Same stray-killvar bug also broke Remove Tattoo From This Zone and Remove Piercing From This Slot in Body Mods - both killed the captured zone/slot before the button using it could be clicked.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.32.1</b>'
'- Changed: Consumables - Individual toggles now read Owned/Not owned instead of Enabled/Disabled, since these are physical items rather than behavior flags.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.32</b>'
'- Fixed: 14 of the items added to Consumables in v0.30 (breastmilk bottles, thrush medication, hair extension shampoo, a butt growth injection, joints/cocaine/amphetamine, foraged berries/mushrooms, and household supplies) are stackable in the base game, not capped at 1 like the items that remain in Individual toggles - moved them into Set All to 10,000/1,000/100 instead of a fixed on/off value.'
'- Added: Consumables - Exercise Equipment toggle category (skipping rope, hula hoop, book on yoga, ice skates, skis, refillable water bottle). These were already granted silently by Set All as part of a generic unique-items grant; pulling them into their own toggles gives each one visibility and individual control, matching the base games own Sport Equipment shop catalog.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.31</b>'
'- Added: Recurrent Cheats - every item in the main list now toggles individually by clicking it, not just via Enable All/Disable All. Also added two cheats the base games own cheat menu has that GLQS was missing entirely: Porn schedule editor and No dream chance (skip bad dreams).'
'- Fixed: Never get addicted, Enable sleeping with vibrator inserted, and Clothes never dirty now call the same handlers the base games own cheat menu uses instead of only flipping the flag, so enabling them also clears existing addiction progress, syncs the bed vibrator setting the sleep menu actually checks, and washes everything currently dirty, matching base game behavior.'
'- Changed: Succubus clothing invulnerability only shows while Clothing archetypes is enabled, matching the base games own cheat menu - it has no effect otherwise.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.30</b>'
'- Added: Consumables now has an Individual toggles section below Set All, covering 20 items the base games own cheat menu and item catalog expose that Set All did not: breastmilk bottles (S/M), thrush medication, hair extension shampoo, a butt growth injection, narcotics (joints, cocaine, amphetamine), bottled water/sandwich/wine, foraged berries and mushrooms, household supplies (dishwashing detergent, clothing detergent, plates), and pregnancy support (morning sickness pills, pregnancy ball/brace/pillow). Kept separate from Set All and toggled individually so items like narcotics are not forced on a playthrough that is not using them - the same reasoning Recurrent Cheats already uses for its own individual toggles.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.13</b>'
'- Fixed: Skills & Attributes listed the def skill as Defence; corrected to Defense to match the base games own skill label.'
'- Changed: Internal cleanup - removed stray excess blank lines that had accumulated in a few src fragments. No player-visible change.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.12</b>'
'- Changed: The Quick Setup link now shows up on every real location in the game (previously only the bedroom, dorm room and therapist hotel room), since it turns out the mod was already being invoked everywhere by the games own mod loader - it was just being filtered down to those 3 screens. Hidden during character creation and the games own scripted scenes (sex scenes, big story beats) so it does not show before your character fully exists or interrupt a scene. Still does not appear during ordinary NPC chat screens, which do not carry a signal this mod can detect.'
'- Fixed: The Return link now returns to the exact screen you opened Quick Setup from, using the same location tracking the game itself uses, instead of a value that was only reliably set if you had recently visited a shop.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.11</b>'
'- Fixed: The Quick Setup link (bedroom/dorm/hotel) was hidden by default on every new save until you found and enabled the Quick Setup Mod toggle buried in the games own cheat menu. Now enabled automatically the first time - the toggle is still there in the cheat menu if you ever want to hide the link.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.10</b>'
'- Removed: The experimental Purse screen Quick Setup link from v0.29.9. Confirmed by live testing it never appeared - the purse is a plain subroutine overlay rather than a real location change, so it does not update the game state the bedroom/dorm/hotel links rely on to detect where the player currently is.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.8</b>'
'- Added: Max Attractiveness button in Body Mods. Forces the underlying appearance base high enough that attractiveness always reads as maxed regardless of clothing, accessories, or grooming state. Only applies until the next in-game day, same as School Grades - click again to reapply.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.7</b>'
'- Fixed: Recurrent Cheats - Impregnation toggle was always shown even while Periods and pregnancies was disabled, where it silently did nothing (conception in the base game only runs as part of the normal menstrual cycle, which Periods and pregnancies fully halts). Now hidden in that state, matching the base games own cheat menu.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.6</b>'
'- Changed: Recurrent Cheats - Impregnation, Lactation, Cum leaking, STDs, Periods and pregnancies, and Clothing archetypes each got their own individual toggle instead of being bundled into Enable All/Disable All, since those six affect more significant game state (fertility, disease risk, clothing-archetype trait progress) than the other quality-of-life toggles. Enable All/Disable All no longer touch these six at all - previously both buttons silently forced all six to the same off state no matter which was clicked, so there was no way to turn any of them on from this menu.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.5</b>'
'- Changed: Internal refactor, no player-visible change. Fame By Region (activity list + labels) was hardcoded in two places (fame_detail and fame_maxregion); they now share one data table, so the copies can no longer drift out of sync. build.py also now checks that mod_info and the changelog version agree, so this specific number cannot silently drift again.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.4</b>'
'- Note: Fame By Region - Max All (this region) only sets that regions own fame directly, but the games own fame-spread system then bleeds some of that into the other regions too (working as designed - e.g. maxing Pavlovsk also pushes Old Town and Gadukino close to maxed, since fame spreads fast between those, while City only gets a small bump since it is slow to notice fame from Pavlovsk). This is base game behavior, not a mod bug.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.3</b>'
'- Fixed: Relationships menu threw a Bracket not found error on open. The v0.29.2 refactor built the NPC value cell as a template marker split across a string concatenation, which QSP does not allow. Now reads npc_rel directly as a value instead of through a template marker.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.2</b>'
'- Changed: Internal refactor, no player-visible change. Relationships (roster + category maxing) and the clothing store catalog (store_buy and the Give Everything handler) each used to hardcode the same NPC list or store/category list in two or three places; they now share one data table each, looped over at render/apply time, so the copies can no longer drift out of sync.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.1</b>'
'- Added: Store icon shown at the top of the store category list and the item picker screen.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29</b>'
'- Changed: Clothing categories (e.g. Allure - Swimsuits) now open an image grid like the tattoo/piercing pickers instead of instantly buying every item in the category. Click an item to add just that one, or use Give All (this category) to still buy the whole category in one click.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.28.2</b>'
'- Changed: Updated the mod description (shown in the games mod list) to cover everything GLQS actually does now - money, relationships, health, body mods and fame were missing from it.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.28.1</b>'
'- Changed: Removed Return to Top Menu from the tattoo design screen (Body Mods, Choose a Tattoo, pick a zone) - Back to Zones already covers it at that depth.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.28</b>'
'- Fixed: Fame By Region (individual activity buttons, Max All This Region, and the live table) still did not apply. Root cause: the region code was captured from ARGS after calling stat/themes, which clobber the shared ARGS array just like any nested gs call, and a stray killvar was clearing the captured region before the player could click a button. Same fix applied to the clothing per-store screen and the tattoo/piercing pickers, which had the same latent bug.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.27</b>'
'- Fixed: Fame maxing (individual activity, Max All This Region, Max All Fame) silently did nothing and the live table always read 0. Root cause: same ARGS clobbering bug as the v0.7 grades fix - re-reading ARGS after a nested gs call back into mod_GLQS_main picked up the callees ARGS instead. Fixed by capturing region/activity into local variables before any nested call.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.26</b>'
'- Added: Fame & Reputation now shows live values - a per-region overview table (Performer, Sex Industry, Slut/Sex Rep, Sport) on the region picker, and a full per-activity fame table on each region screen, matching the Skills & Attributes style.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.25</b>'
'- Added: Fame & Reputation submenu now has a By Region breakdown (Pavlovsk, City, Old Town, Gadukino) with an individual Max button per activity, plus a Max All (this region) option, alongside the existing Max All Fame (everything) button.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.24</b>'
'- Added: Fame & Reputation submenu with a Max All Fame button covering every activity (acting, dance, painting, music, ballet, modelling, porn, stripping, kickboxing, running, volleyball, chess, teaching, media, sex, prostitution, flashing) across all four regions.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.23</b>'
'- Added: Every submenu now has a Return to Top Menu button that jumps straight back to the main Quick Setup screen, in addition to any existing one-level-back navigation.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.22</b>'
'- Added: Buy By Store submenu now breaks each store down into individual category buttons (e.g. Panties, Bras, Outfits, Shoes) instead of one buy-everything action, plus a Buy All (this store) option.'
'- Fixed: Store category submenu used single-line if statements with a trailing end, which QSP does not allow - it desynced block parsing for the rest of mod_GLQS_main and caused an Unknown action error. Removed the invalid end from every single-line if.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.21</b>'
'- Added: Per-category [Max] link next to each relationship category header (Family, Popular Kids, Athletes, Nerds, Gopniks, Outcasts, Teachers, Others), respecting the gender filter.'
'- Changed: Tattoo/piercing image galleries now use a wrapping grid layout instead of stacking vertically.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.20</b>'
'- Changed: Body Mods now lets you pick a zone/slot and browse actual tattoo and piercing designs by image, instead of a single Give All button. Electrolysis unchanged.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.19</b>'
'- Fixed: Apostrophes inside !! comments (e.g. games, cheat_repair) broke the parser - the game engine does not fully suppress quote-parsing inside comments, so a lone apostrophe opened an unterminated string that corrupted all block-nesting after it. Removed all apostrophes from comments.'
'- Changed: Individual store buttons in Clothing & Accessories moved behind a Buy By Store submenu.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.18</b>'
'- Added: Per-store buy-out buttons in Clothing & Accessories.'
'- Fixed: Clothing no longer needs tailor repair/resize. Root cause was the companion _h[] durability array never being set, defaulting to 0.'
'- Added: Body Mods submenu (free electrolysis, tattoo every zone, piercing every slot).'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.17</b>'
'- Added: Money submenu (open bank account, give cash/bank funds).'
'- Added: Relationships submenu showing and maxing key NPC relationships.'
'- Added: Health & Energy submenu with full restore.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.16.1</b>'
'- Added: Consumables submenu now has Set All to 10,000 / 1,000 / 100 options.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.15</b>'
'- Removed: Do Everything option.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.14</b>'
'- Fixed: Max All Skills & Attributes was redirecting to the cheat menu. setSkills and setAttrs both end with gt cheatmenu_din which hijacks navigation. Replaced with direct setStat calls for every skill and attribute.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.13</b>'
'- Added: Clothing, Consumables and Skills & Attributes all now open their own submenus showing live data before applying changes.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.12</b>'
'- Changed: Grades moved to its own submenu showing live grade values.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.11</b>'
'- Fixed: Grades re-added. Root cause: grade_cap=0 clamped all grade_award calls to 0 in nested gs context. Fixed with 13 flat direct calls.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.9</b>'
'- Fixed: Consumables completely rewritten using correct mc_inventory[''name''] system.'
'- All old variable names (prezikcount, tampon, etc.) were legacy/wrong - replaced with 67 correct mc_inventory keys.'
'- Added full coverage: beauty, medical, contraceptives, drugs, food, sex toys, magazines, unique equipment.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.8</b>'
'- Dropped: Grades support removed. The grade system requires school initialization (createclass/grade_cap) that cannot be reliably set from a mod context.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.7</b>'
'- Fixed: Grade variables now set class cap to 100 before assigning grade directly.'
'- Fixed: ARGS[1] was being clobbered by inner gs calls inside fill_grade loop.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.6</b>'
'- Fixed: Syntax error caused by inline !! comments after code (QSP only supports !! at start of a line).'
'- Fixed: Em dash characters in comments caused parser crash.'
'- Fixed: Attributes now use gs ''shortgs'', ''setStat'' directly (setAttrs needed $att_name[] pre-populated at startup).'
'- Fixed: Grade storage uses class[''school_X_grade''] not gschoolVars. Grades are 0-100 not 1-5.'
'- Fixed: Inhibition raw value is inverted - 100 = uninhibited, 0 = fully inhibited.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.5</b>'
'- Fixed: Inline !! comments partially addressed. Attribute variable names corrected from game source.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.4</b>'
'- Fixed: Skill and attribute variable names corrected using cheatmenu_din source code.'
'- Added: Skills, attributes and grades option (grades still broken at this point).'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.3</b>'
'- Added: Max Skills / Attributes / Grades option (all variable names wrong, fixed in later versions).'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.2</b>'
'- Fixed: Clothing now unlocks from ALL stores, not just visited ones.'
'- Root cause: arrsize() returns 0 for unvisited store arrays. Fixed by using each category totals subroutine.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.1 - Initial Release</b>'
'- All clothing and accessories from every store.'
'- 10,000 of all consumables (variable names were wrong, fixed in 0.9).'
*nl
act 'Return': gt 'mod_setting'
--- mod_GLQS_readme ---------------------------------
